-- European Thermal Coal for Next Year Drops as Crude Oil Declines
-- B y   J u l i a   M e n g e w e i n
-- 2013-02-19T16:05:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-19/european-thermal-coal-for-next-year-drops-as-crude-oil-declines.html
European coal for 2014 delivery
dropped as crude oil prices declined.  Thermal coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or
Antwerp lost as much as 0.3 percent to $98.70 a metric ton and
traded at $98.85 at 4 p.m. London time, according to broker data
compiled by Bloomberg. The contract has lost 17 percent in the
past 12 months. Brent crude for April settlement dropped as much
as 0.7% to $116.55 a barrel on the London-based ICE Futures
Europe Exchange.  Bloomberg tracks information from ICAP Plc, GFI Group Inc.,
Marex Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julia Mengewein in Frankfurt at 
